    <h1>üöÄ Unlocking Text Insights: Sentiment Analysis & Keyword Extraction üöÄ</h1>

    <p>Ever wondered what the underlying sentiment of a text is, or which words stand out most? This project, built with <strong>Streamlit</strong>, provides a simple yet powerful interface for <span class="highlight"><strong>text analysis</strong></span>, focusing on <strong>sentiment analysis</strong> and <strong>frequent keyword extraction</strong>. It's designed to give quick, actionable insights into any given text, from news articles to customer feedback.</p>

    <div class="section-divider"></div>

    <h2>‚ú® Features at a Glance</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Sentiment Analysis (TextBlob):</strong> Get an objective polarity score (from -1 for negative to +1 for positive) and a subjectivity score (from 0 for objective to 1 for subjective). Understand the overall emotional tone.</li>
        <li><strong>Advanced Sentiment Analysis (Hugging Face Transformers):</strong> Leverage state-of-the-art pre-trained models for a more nuanced sentiment classification (e.g., POSITIVE, NEGATIVE, NEUTRAL) with a confidence score.</li>
        <li><strong>Top 10 Frequent Words Chart:</strong> Visualize the most commonly used words in your text (after removing common "stop words" like "the," "a," etc.) to quickly grasp key themes.</li>
        <li><strong>Dynamic Word Cloud:</strong> See a visually engaging representation of your text's most prominent terms, where word size reflects its frequency.</li>
        <li><strong>Intuitive Interface:</strong> A user-friendly Streamlit application makes text analysis accessible to anyone ‚Äì no coding required!</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="section-divider"></div>

    <h2>üí° Why This Matters</h2>
    <p>In today's data-rich world, understanding text is crucial. This tool can be incredibly valuable for:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Market Research:</strong> Quickly gauge public opinion on products or services.</li>
        <li><strong>Social Media Monitoring:</strong> Understand the sentiment around brands or events.</li>
        <li><strong>Customer Feedback Analysis:</strong> Identify common pain points or praises in reviews.</li>
        <li><strong>Content Creation:</strong> Optimize content for a desired emotional impact.</li>
        <li><strong>Academic Research:</strong> Analyze large bodies of text for thematic patterns.</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="section-divider"></div>

    <h2>üõ†Ô∏è Technologies Used</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Python:</strong> The core programming language.</li>
        <li><strong>Streamlit:</strong> For building the interactive web application.</li>
        <li><strong>TextBlob:</strong> A simplified text processing library for sentiment analysis.</li>
        <li><strong>Hugging Face Transformers:</strong> For advanced, pre-trained NLP models.</li>
        <li><strong>NLTK (Natural Language Toolkit):</strong> For robust text tokenization and stop word removal.</li>
        <li><strong>Matplotlib & Pandas:</strong> For data visualization and manipulation.</li>
        <li><strong>WordCloud:</strong> To generate beautiful word cloud visualizations.</li>
    </ul>

